item.description:
@Original_Daniel wrote:

[quote=“davidude36, post:2, topic:238461”]OD, pretty sure its a hard ware problem. I get this a heck of a lot. It saves to your desktop as hs_err_pid#### right?[/quote]Yeah.

It couldn’t be overheating though, I have like 7 fans in my computer.

On another topic

Is it a problem with jre or does it only happen in that game? The designers shouldn’t have built something based on the Java platform if it doesn’t work with the latest version.

I don’t think it’s the game.

item.title: An unexpected error has been detected by JRE
item.dc:creator: @davidude36 Brolapse
item.description:
@davidude36 wrote:

OD, pretty sure its a hard ware problem. I get this a heck of a lot. It saves to your desktop as hs_err_pid#### right?

I find that it’s usually because some part of my computer is overheating, namely my ram. So if I start getting this my way to fix it is to get my handy deskfan on and aim it into the computer with the sides of the case off. 99% of the time I stop getting the errors.

Of course this is a shitty fix and I should really get it sorted, and of course your problem could be completely different to mine.

Read full topic
